<!DOCTYPE solution PUBLIC "-//SIMPLACE/DTD SOL 1.0//EN" "http://simplace.net/dtd/SimSolution_4_1.dtd">

<solution version="4.1" check="LAZY">
  <description title="Solution reproduces results of the Fortran Lintul5 Version" author="Gunther Krauss" qualitylevel="II">
    WIKI_START
      === Purpose ===
      - Serve as a general example for documenting the simulations of a research project
      - Test the implementation of Lintul5 and to compare the results with the output of 
        the original fortran program (original purpose).

      === References ===
      This solution uses standard parameters and data that is provided with the Lintul5 package from
      the Model Library of the Plant Production Systems, Wageningen, Netherlands 

      [http://models.pps.wur.nl/content/lintul-5-crop-growth-simulation-model-potential-water-limited-n-limited-and-npk-limited-co-0 Link]

      Executable program, fortran source code, input and output data can be downloaded as a .zip file from the link above. 

      === Data ====
      Data (parameters, weather data) was derived from following files from the directory Test-L-NPK
      * (B) BATCH.INP - batch input file that controls the run
      * (S) SOILP1.DAT - default soil parameters
      * (C) CROPP1.DAT - default crop parameters (winter wheat)
      * (W) SEVI87.dat - weather file for 1987
      * (M) MANAGE.DAT - default management
      * (O) WAGIPTS1.dat - output of the fortran program 

      Data has been converted to the required data format. Values whose original units contain kg, ha, cm were
      transformed to g, m^2 and mm (water) resp. m (lengths).

      === Remarks ===
      The output of this solution is (up to rounding errors) the same as the fortran program (O).

      === Usage ====
      * Used with simplace-project SimulationExperimentTemplate/projects/Lintul5All.proj.xml to calculate all scenarios from (B)
      * Test if Simplace&lt;Lintul5&gt; produces same results as the original fortran program.
      * UnitTest to assert the same results when changes are made to the framework/component (comparison is not yet automatic)
      * Variation of this solution (changing vIOPT and vLocation) was used to compare with other results produced by original program
      * Solution used as a starting point by other users to implement their Lintul5-based solutions.
    WIKI_END
  </description>

